metadata.name: Ethereal Microcosm #79
metadata.description:
An exploration of algorithmic organisms in a contained environment.

This piece is about the simulation of microscopic patterns using a high number of even tinier agents all following the same rules. Different species evolve and interact together, resulting in stabilizing patterns out of their parametric configurations. A form of artificial life.

This work is based on the paper "Characteristics of pattern formation and evolution in approximations of physarum transport networks", written by Jeff Jones and popularized in the artistic field by Sage Jenson. Some features were added to increase the visual and behavioral complexity of the system. Agents are divided into different species, with their own set of rules and interacting with their own substrate. Substrates also interact with each other and agents will mutate in contact of some of them.

NFT License
Runs properly on Chrome 97.0.4692.99
GPU intensive

Press P to pause (double tab touch devices)
Press

metadata.name: Charcoal Seeds #316
metadata.description:
As a fundamental element derived from organic matter, charcoal happens to be at the core of all life forms. It is also the tool for artists that dates back to the most ancient times. 
By using charcoal as the the primary medium for the exhibition ‚ÄòOrganic Matr‚Äô (and resulting series of physical pieces created in collaboration with Brooklyn-based lab ArtMatr), the works creates bonds between technology and the rawest tool that was touched by the human hand, and highlights how the cycle of life is also the cycle of regeneration of matter.

Since the generative process _that uses programming code and the intervention of randomness_ was used to design the physical pieces, the long-form generative series Charcoal Seeds is a natural way to seamlessly extend back into the digital realm the ideas of matter and physicality, while showing the elements at work in the creation process. 
In each iteration a virtual seed will encapsulates the essence of organic forms and patterns. The graphic style itself tries to convey the organic feeling of tools and materials such as chalk, ink, paintbrushes. 


‚Äî‚Äî 

- "Charcoal Seeds" offers a WYSIWYG experience : by deriving the randomness from the minter‚Äôs wallet address, it is guaranteed that what you see onscreen after adjusting the params will be your actual NFT. 
However, we wanted to allow the possibility of getting some rare features. By selecting "random" for the Format or the Paper color, you will get a chance to mint a Pink or a Back background, or have a Wide Landscape format. Beware : this will break the WYSIWYG ( but it will keep your params settings safe ) 

- As usual, the project is plottable : press [s] in live mode to generate a SVG file suited for pen plotters.

- By adding a ‚Äòscale‚Äô parameter in the live URL, you can generate a higher resolution image. The scale ranges from 1 to 10 with a default value of 3.

metadata.name: Orbit of Influence #118
metadata.description:
Orbit of Influence is part of the fxhash live minting experience at Proof of People, ZeroSpace NYC, 2023 and is a unique generative program created using processing's p5js and SVG. Developed from scratch, it employs a system of rule-based environments that have been a source of satisfaction for me since 1995.

The program generates three invisible planets, each at a different scale - small, medium, and large. Fifty objects then randomly select a planet, a speed to orbit around it, and one of three brush sizes - small, medium, or large. These objects move around their respective planets, painting color and texture across the planetary orbit in three-dimensional space.

To reveal the blueprint of the system, press the "s" key on your keyboard. The hidden algorithm that governs the brushes' movement is then displayed, revealing a mesmerizing display of synchronized choreography as the brushes interconnect with each other.

Press the following keys to interact :

- '1': swap the background color to "ocean"
- '2': swap the background color to "mist"
- '3': swap the background color to "lilac"
- '4': swap the background color to "amethyst"
- '5': swap the background color to "crimson"
- '6': swap the background color to "emerald"

- 'l': toggle animation loop on/off
- 's': system reveal, show the blueprint of the algorithm

Joshua Davis / PrayStation 'Orbit of Influence' / (2023) real-time generative program, 1240 x 1653 px, Date Minted: April 2023

Twitter: @joshuadavis
Instagram: @praystation
Website: https://joshuadavis.com

Bio :

Since 1995, Joshua Davis is an artist, technologist, author and designer in algorithmic image making & animation. Using programming, he writes his own code to produce interactions with users and to generate visual compositions according to rule-based, randomized processes.

Joshua has exhibited his works and/or lectured at the Ars Electronica (Austria), Centre Georges Pompidou (France), Contemporary Arts Center (Cincinnati), J. Paul Getty Museum (Los Angeles),  the Tate Modern (London), the Design Museum (London), the Institute of Contemporary Arts (London), PS.1 MoMA (New York), the Whitney (New York), the Smithsonian‚Äôs Cooper-Hewitt National Design Museum (New York), the Guggenheim Museum Bilbao (Spain), among others.

Since 2000, Joshua has lectured globally about his work, inspirations and motivations at museums, galleries, institutions, art festivals, etc., and has spoken at the TED (2005) and 99U (2013) conferences about his career in algorithmic image making and open source.

metadata.name: pure  #61
metadata.description:
A polygon is generated by a random number of vertices. Each polygon consists of triangles which are connected to each other. The vertices receive pure color values from Red Green Blue, which also can create Magenta Yellow Cyan as well Black and White. Each vertex also gets an opacity value.
The colors are blended between the neighboring vertices and create a unique colored polygon.
The vertices occupy specific positions in space which are reflected in the background and become observable during the rotation of the construct.
Canvas and background receive colors per token as well to create different oppositions to the object.
The polygon rotates slowly to experience a mixture of a two and three dimensional experience.
Additionally the perspective can be adjusted for a quicker rotation around the object.

metadata.name: Paper Mandala #216
metadata.description:
A collaboration with P1xelboy and Paper Buddha.
Beautiful paper mandalas made purely with code in Paper Buddha's style.
Features include:
27 different palettes
3 different mandala types (Lotus, Starburst Style 1 and Starburst Style 2)
Four sections of the mandala with one of 10 different pattern types (Dots, Checks, Crosses, Triangles, Stripes, Circles, Polygons, Lazers, Quadrants and Hatching)
4 different direction types of shadow - of varying length
Randomly placed star background
Randomly placed Nebula
Possible Special Pattern Effect with darker stippling pattern
Possible Nirvana Effect where random colors are added to one of either Golden, Silver, Bronze, Blue Moon or Sea Green palettes.

Using only code, this produces a unique output which does take a few seconds to load.
Press "S" to Save your unique Paper Mandala as a 2048 x 2048 JPG
Press "R" for a random shuffle effect - (please wait for reload) - Refresh page to reset

The project works in a responsive browser, so to set up for phone background or watch, resize the browser accordingly and Alt + Print Screen to get an appropriately sized image.

Offered as a Dutch Auction, holders of the first 20 tokens (1-20) will receive additional benefits in the form of utility for future releases in the P1xelboy/Paper Mandala collaboration series. (exact details to be determined)
This utility will remain attached to tokens 1-20 and transfer to the new owner upon subsequent secondary sales.

Uses p5.js and p5.pattern
@p1x3lboy @paperbuddha - September 2022

metadata.name: ReAssembled #78
metadata.description:
As we each grapple with artificial intelligence (love it or hate it), it‚Äôs a technological advance that is here to stay and we must all wrestle with what makes it different from us humans. Both humans and AI learn and transform through others - might our experiences just be very complex training models? 

‚ÄúReAssembled‚Äù reflects on the truth that we are all constantly evolving and growing through the visual metaphor of Frankenstein‚Äôs creation. However, this process of growth is not unique to humans nor reanimated life. 

AI also learns and transforms through the data that it processes. The portraits in this project are a visual representation of this idea. They are a product of AI's ability to learn, grow and reassemble data, just as we humans do with our own experiences.

The project was created with the conception, design, and digital painting (by a human), with portraits generated by AI and layers all stitched together using the magic of code written by another human. 

The title "ReAssembled" references the process of creating the final image and the dark assemblage of Victor Frankenstein‚Äôs creation, but it also speaks to the idea of reassembling our own identities, and how our experiences shape us. 

I hope that this project sparks reflection on the complexity of the human experience and the inseparable role that technology plays in it.

~~~~~
-Minters get 4% royalty
-Collectors of The Modern Prometheus get a 24hr reserve
-33% of primary goes to Tezos for Iran, supporting women‚Äôs rights in Iran.

Trait list:
9 faces with equal rarity in each quadrant
13 ‚Äúscars‚Äù of varying rarity
7 mouths of varying rarity
11 eyes of varying rarity

Special Trait:
‚ÄúCrowned‚Äù scar trait will get 3 free mints of my next Fx Hash project.

6.5 million potential variations

~~~
Special thanks to PureSpider for his template.
